race.description: The Daily Advertiser Country Boosted Mdn Hcp
race.comment: Tricky race to assess with a stack of first starters engaged, and a lot of them trialling well in readiness. I'M CHARMING (2) is a debutant by sire Headwater, from the stakes winner Johanski. Impressed at his only barrier trial, and with it over the 1000m here, a bright start is anticipated. STERN LOOKS (1) was good on debut when finishing second at Moruya. Don't see too many examples of runners making their debuts at five. Admire the patience of connections and their patience suggests he should be shedding his maiden tag at some point soon assuming he stays sound. GOBINDA (9) showed good improvement second up when fourth at this course a fortnight ago. SUPER NIC (3) next elect.
